  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q001094.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(i 1) For Ninĝirsu , Enlil’s warrior ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001094.3",
      "line_range": "3",
      "translation": "(i 3) En-metena , ruler of Lagaš , child of En-ana-tum , ruler of Lagaš , built the great temple of Antasura for Ninĝirsu , and decorated it with gold and silver . He constructed the garden of the personal quarters , and installed numerous wells of fired brick in it for him ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001094.17",
      "line_range": "17",
      "translation": "(ii 8) At that time , his servant Dudu , the temple administrator of Ninĝirsu , built the wall alongside Sala in Gu-edena , and named it for his sake \" The temple is the guard against the plain \". He built the wall of the ferry harbour in Ĝirsu , and named it for his sake “The lord is vigour” ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001094.31",
      "line_range": "31",
      "translation": "(iv 4) May his personal god , Šul-MUŠxPA , pay obeisance to Ninĝirsu in the E-ninnu for his well-being !"
    }
  ],
